 and Lawrence Honig and Y. Stern and A. Mintz and Jonathan Cordona and Michelle Hernandez and J. Long and Abbey Arnold and Alexandrer Groves and Anna Middleton and Blake Vogler and Cierra McCurry and Connie Mayo and Cyrus Raji and Fatima S. Amtashar and Heather Klemp and Heather Nicole Elmore and J. Ruszkiewicz and Jasmina Kusuran and Jasmine Stewart and Jennifer Horenkamp and Julia L Greeson and Kara Wever and Katie Vo and Kelly Larkin and Lesley Rao and Lisa Schoolcraft and Lora Gallagher and Madeline Paczynski and Maureen McMillan and Michael Holt and Nicole Gagliano and Rachel Henson and Renee LaBarge and R. Swarm and Sarah Munie and Serena Cepeda and S. Winterton and Stephen Hegedus and TaNisha Wilson and Tanya Harte and Zach Bonacorsi and D. Geldmacher and Amber Watkins and Brandi Barger and Bryan Smelser and Charna Bates and Cynthia Stover and Emily McKinley and Gregory Ikner and Haley Hendrix and H. Cooper and J. Mahaffey and Lindsey Booth Robbins and Loren Brown Ashley and Marissa Natelson-Love and Princess Carter and Veronika Solomon and Hillel Grossman and Alexandra Groome and Allison Ardolino and Anthony Kaplan and Faye Sheppard and Genesis Burgos-Rivera and Gina Garcia-Camilo and Joanne Lim and J. Neugroschl and Kimberly Jackson and Kirsten Evans and L. Soleimani and Mary Sano and N. Ghesani and Sarah Binder and Xiomara Mendoza Apuango and Ajay Sood and Amelia Troutman and K. Blanchard and Arlene D Richards and Grace Nelson and Kirsten Hendrickson and Erin Yurko and Jamie Plenge and Victoria Rufo and R. Shah and R. Duara and Brendan Lynch and Cesar L. Chirinos and Christine Dittrich and Debbie Campbell and Diego Mejia and Gilberto Perez and Helena Colvee and Joanna Gonzalez and Josalen Gondrez and Joshua Knaack and Maria Acevedo and M. Cereijo and M. Greig‐Custo and M. Villar and Morris Wishnia and Sheryl Detling and W. Barker and Marilyn S. Albert and A. Moghekar and Barbara Rodzon and Corey Demsky and Gregory Pontone and Jim Pekar and L. Farrington and Martin Pomper and Nicole Johnson and Tolulope Alo and M. Sadowski and A. Ulysse and Arjun Masurkar and Brittany Marti and David Mossa and Emilie Geesey and Emily Petrocca and Evan Schulze and Jennifer Wong and Joseph Boonsiri and S. Kenowsky and Tatianne Martinez and Veronica Briglall and P. Doraiswamy and A. Nwosu and Alisa Adhikari and Cammie Hellegers and J. Petrella and O. James and T. Wong and Thomas Hawk and S. Vaishnavi and Hannah McCoubrey and I. Nasrallah and Rachel Rovere and Jeffrey Maneval and Elizabeth Robinson and Francisco Rivera and J. Uffelman and Martha Combs and Patricia O'Donnell and Sara Manning and Richard D. King and Alayne Nieto and Amanda Glueck and Anjana Mandal and Audrie Swain and B. Gamble and Beverly Meacham and Denece Forenback and Dorothy Ross and Elizabeth Cheatham and Ellen Hartman and Gary Cornell and Jordan P. Harp and Laura Ashe and Laura Goins and Linda Watts and Morgan Yazell and Prabin Mandal and Regan Buckler and Sylvia Vincent and Triana Rudd and Oscar L. Lopez and Ann Arlene Malia and Caitlin Chiado and Cary Zik and Kathleen Savage and Linda Fenice and M. Oakley and Paige C. Tacey and Sarah Berman and Sarah Bowser and Xanthia Saganis and A. Porsteinsson and Abigail Mathewson and Asa Widman and Bridget Holvey and Emily Clark and Esmeralda Morales and I. Young and Kevin Hopkins and K. Martin and N. Kowalski and Rebecca Hunt and Roberta Calzavara and Russell Kurvach and Stephen M. D’Ambrosio and G. Thai and Beatriz Vides and Brigit Lieb and Catherine McAdams-Ortiz and Cyndy Toso and Ivan Mares and Kathryn Moorlach and Luter Liu and Maria Corona and M. Nguyen and Melanie B Tallakson and Michelle McDonnell and Milagros Rangel and Neetha Basheer and Patricia Place and Romina Romero and S. Tam and Trung Nguyen and Abey Thomas and Alka Khera and Amy Browning and Brendan Kelley and C. Dawson and D. Mathews and Elaine Most and Lynn G. Nguyen and Maribel Nunez and Matalin Miller and Matthew R. Jones and Natalie Martinez and Rebecca Logan and R. McColl and Sari Pham and Tiffani Fox and Tracey Moore and A. Levey and Abby Brown and Andrea Kippels and Ashton Ellison and C. Lyons and Chadwick M. Hales and Cindy Parry and Courtney Williams and Elizabeth McCorkle and Guy Harris and Heather Rose and Inara Jooma and Jahmila Al‐Amin and James J. Lah and James Webster and Jessica Swiniarski and Latasha Chapman and Laura Donnelly and Lauren Mariotti and Mary Locke and Phyllis Vaughn and Rachael Penn and S. Carpentier and Samira Yeboah and Sarah Basadre and Sarah Malakauskas and Stefka Lyron and Tara Villinger and Terra Burney and J. Burns and Ala Abusalim and Alexandra Dahlgren and Alexandria Montero and Anne Arthur and Heather Dooly and Katelynn Kreszyn and Katherine Berner and Lindsey Gillen and Maria Scanlan and Mercedes Madison and Nicole Mathis and Phyllis Switzer and Ryan Townley and Samantha Fikru and Samantha Sullivan and Ella Wright},
  year = {2026},
  abstract = {Summary Background The glymphatic system plays a critical role in brain waste clearance and health. Diffusion tensor imaging along the perivascular space (DTI-ALPS) is an emerging approach to assess glymphatic function, but manual analysis is limited by its subjectivity and laboriousness in clinical practice. To address these challenges, we developed a deep learning-enhanced DTI-ALPS (dALPS) method that automates and enhances measurement of DTI-ALPS in large-scale cohorts, enabling us to uncover its genetic and environmental determinants. Methods We proposed an automated workflow combining convolutional neural network (CNN) and You Only Look Once (YOLO) for region-of-interest detection in DTI images. Using this method, we calculated dALPS index for over 65,000 participants from UK Biobank and multiple cohorts, and performed a genome-wide association study (GWAS). Additionally, we conducted transcriptome-wide association study (TWAS) and proteome-wide association study (PWAS) to explore the genetic and molecular underpinnings of glymphatic function. Associations between dALPS and demographic, lifestyle, and clinical traits were comprehensively evaluated. Mediation analysis was conducted to explore the potential mediating role of pharmacological treatments, including antidepressants and sleep medications, in the relationship between disease status and dALPS outcomes. Findings Our automated dALPS index showed excellent reliability and reproducibility compared to conventional manual techniques (intraclass correlation coefficient = 0·95). We observed that the dALPS index was associated with a wide range of body composition measures and brain structures across different age groups and sex. GWAS identified five significant genetic loci associated with dALPS, two of which were replicated in an independent dataset. Subsequent TWAS and PWAS analyses highlighted potential causal genes and proteins linked to brain fluid dynamics. We found that higher healthy lifestyle index (HLI) was positively correlated with improved dALPS, and confirmed the associations between reduced dALPS and various central nervous system (CNS) disorders, including depression, anxiety and neurodegenerative diseases. Notably, mediation analysis indicated that antidepressants were a risk factor for lower brain glymphatic function (P = 0·004) by partly mediating the risk factor of depression. Interpretation The dALPS analysis provides a reliable, precise, and automated biomarker for assessing brain glymphatic function. Our findings illuminate the genetic and environmental determinants of glymphatic activity, underscoring the potential of dALPS in clinical assessment, disease prediction and targeted therapeutic strategies. Funding G.L.’s work is supported by 10.13039/501100001809National Natural Science Foundation of China (No. 32470708, No. 32270701), 10.13039/501100017607Shenzhen Fundamental Research Program (JCYJ20240813151132042), Young Talent Recruitment Project of Guangdong (2019QN01Y139), Shenzhen Key Laboratory for Systems Medicine in Inflammatory Diseases (ZDSYS20220606100803007) and The Science and Technology Planning Project of Guangdong Province (2023B1212060018). Z.P.’s work is supported by National Natural Science Foundation of China (No. 82271266) and The Shenzhen Medical Research Fund (C2501030).},
  doi = {10.1016/j.ebiom.2026.106133},
  pmid = {41619353},
